Harmony is the largest gold producer by volume in South Africa and is a significant operator of gold tailings retreatment facilities. In Papua New Guinea, Harmony owns and operates the Hidden Valley mine and owns 50% of the Tier 1 Wafi-Golpu copper-gold project. In Australia, Harmony owns the high-grade CSA copper mine in Cobar, NSW and is constructing the Eva Copper Mine in Cloncurry, QLD with first production targeted for the second half of the 2028 calendar year. These assets are supported by the Harmony Australasia regional corporate office located in Milton, Brisbane.

We are seeking a motivated and experienced Group Business Improvement Manager to join our team based in Milton, Brisbane.

Reporting to the EGM – Processing and Operational Projects, you will lead, govern, and embed a culture of continuous improvement across Harmony Australasia’s processing and operational business units. The Group Business Improvement Manager is responsible for the development, ownership, and continuous enhancement of the Business Improvement (BI) framework, ensuring it is robust, scalable, and aligned with corporate objectives. This role sets strategic direction, oversees implementation, and ensures best practices are adopted group wide.

The key responsibilities of this role include:

Strategic & Operational Alignment

Define and govern the group-wide Business Improvement (BI) strategy, ensuring alignment with corporate and site objectives.

Integrate BI initiatives into planning, budgeting, and operational systems.

Advise senior leadership on priorities and resource allocation.

Initiative Management

Sponsor and oversee major cross-functional improvement projects.

Ensure consistent use of methodologies (Lean, TOC, Agile, Six Sigma).

Track and report outcomes using group-wide systems (e.g., MOS, Ripple, Wave).

Capability Building

Develop and deliver BI training programs for managers and frontline teams.

Mentor BI Managers and promote BI tools and frameworks across units.

Culture & Engagement

Foster a culture of ownership, creativity, and collaboration.

Create forums for sharing best practices and celebrate successes.

Technology Integration

Collaborate with digital teams to embed technology in BI initiatives.

Oversee deployment of automation, digital twins, and analytics platforms.

Management Operating System (MOS)

Design and maintain the group-wide MOS for planning, execution, and monitoring.

Ensure alignment with BI framework and provide training for adoption.

Site & Business Unit Engagement

Conduct regular site visits to support BI implementation.

Facilitate workshops and improvement sessions for alignment and momentum.

About You:

To succeed in this role, you should be self-motivated and able to work efficiently and collaboratively with: 

Tertiary education in either Engineering / Financial / Commercial.

MBA or equivalent postgraduate qualification preferred.

15+ years’ experience in Six Sigma, Lean, Agile, and constraint modelling, with at least 5 years in a senior or group-level role.

Advanced data science/analytics expertise.

Proven success in developing, owning, and governing business improvement frameworks at a multi-site or group level.

Exceptional communication and influencing skills at executive and board levels.

What are the benefits of working for Harmony?

Flexible working practises.

Eligible to participate in the company bonus scheme.

Corporate / discounted rates with Medibank and Qantas Club.

Access to Harmony’s benefits discounts scheme.

The opportunity to work for an international mining company with a diverse workforce.

To Apply:

If you believe you have the skills, knowledge and experience to fulfil this role, please submit your application online. Please include a Cover Letter which outlines how your skills and experience align with this role.

Salary will be negotiated commensurate with experience.

Please note: All candidates must have the right to live and work in Australia be to be considered for this role. The successful candidate will be required to undertake a pre-employment medical screen, including drug and alcohol testing.

We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and have grown to become a top 30-listed company on the ASX with a portfolio of iconic homegrown brands. About the team

Our Finance team are a vital partner in every aspect of our business, providing commercial insights to drive our success and influence everything we do. With presence in every department, we analyse performance, and deliver actionable insights that shape our strategic decisions.

About the role


As part of a highly visible team, you’ll play a critical role in driving business decision-making and ensuring alignment across the organisation. This position is central to delivering the planning cycle and supporting strategic initiatives that shape the future of the business. Your responsibilities will include:



Facilitate and deliver the business planning cycle, ensuring alignment across all parts of the business.
Support business-wide planning processes including budget and multi-year strategic planning.
Ensure delivery of Board and Executive Leadership team requirements and decision-making information, providing accurate insights.
Drive Coles Group planning processes liaising with wider finance team and strategy on deliverables & timelines.

About you and your skills

You’ll bring strong financial expertise and a collaborative approach to problem-solving. Your ability to manage complex data, build relationships, and influence stakeholders will be key to success in this role. As the successful candidate, you will have:



CA/CPA qualified in addition to finance background preferably covering financial control, FP&A or commercial decision support.
Finance experience in a retail or FMCG environment desirable.
Understanding of standard financial KPIs across the P&L, balance sheet and cash flow.
Ability to establish relationships and cross-functional partnerships across the business.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.

Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. Principal Strategic Business Consultant - Permanent Full Time - Perth CBD





Western Power is a government-owned utility responsible for planning, building and operating Western Australia's electricity network, playing a critical role in enabling the state's energy transition and major decarbonisation initiatives.

This role operates as a trusted advisor to the Head of Engineering and Design, and the selected candidate will join as a member of the leadership team of this large engineering function.

This is high-impact strategic role suited for a seasoned consulting professional seeking to transition from advisory to leadership influence within a critical infrastructure organisation. We are looking for strategic experience in the rapid diagnosis of complex operating model issues and translating insight into clear, executive-ready advice.

When issues arise or opportunities emerge, the role conducts targeted analysis of financial, operational, and workforce data to identify root causes and develop practical, executive-ready recommendations. Working closely with senior leaders across Western Power, the role shapes executive communications, drives targeted business improvements, and delivers measurable outcomes. The role is focused on practical execution, pace, and delivering measurable business impact.

Your Role in Action

Develop high-impact executive presentations and decision-making packs; collect and synthesise complex data to support strategic recommendations and business storytelling.
Facilitate strategic planning workshops, contribute to board papers and business cases, and translate business strategy into actionable initiatives with clear success criteria.
Collaborate with stakeholders to define and refine enterprise project, program, and portfolio management frameworks that enhance organisational maturity and delivery capability.
Identify, manage, and deliver functional improvement projects within Engineering and Design, ensuring timely execution and adherence to budget.
Conduct regular, data-driven analysis of functional performance to uncover risks and opportunities, champion innovation and continuous improvement to foster a culture of excellence.
Design and implement KPIs, monitoring systems, and reporting frameworks aligned with organisational strategy to support functional excellence.
Identify relevant performance benchmarks by developing a network with other leading utilities around the world.
Provide timely and insightful reporting of research findings, analysis, and business intelligence to support informed decision-making.
Serve as a key liaison for triaging operational queries and enabling leadership to focus on strategic, high-value initiatives.
Partner with other senior leaders across the business to align work allocation and commercial activities with operational priorities and organisational goals.

Senior Data Analyst
 
Own the numbers that shape how a high-growth tech company scales.
 
In a nutshell
This is a senior, hands-on role for a data analyst who cares deeply about accuracy, clarity, and commercial impact. You'll own Removify's core metrics, dashboards, and reporting, creating a trusted source of truth that helps the business understand what's driving performance, where to focus, and what decisions actually matter.
 
We're a data-rich, operations-heavy business with proprietary systems, high volume, and global growth ambitions. This role isn't about producing more dashboards, it's about producing better insight, challenging assumptions, and making data genuinely useful as we scale.
 
If you enjoy translating messy, complex data into clear, actionable insight and aren't afraid to say "that metric won't help", this role is for you.
 
Why Removify?
Removify is a fast-growing digital reputation management company operating at scale across Australia, the US, and other global markets. We combine customer-facing products with complex internal operational systems that power how we deliver services at volume.
 
As the business has grown, so has the importance of our data. We sit on a unique mix of commercial, operational, and product data, creating real opportunities to improve performance, efficiency, and decision-making.
 
This is a chance to step into a senior, high-impact analytics role where your work directly influences how the business operates and scales.
 
What you'll be owning
You'll take full ownership of our core analytics layer, from definitions through to insight.
 
Metrics, Definitions & Source of Truth

Own and maintain the data dictionary and KPI definitions
Establish a single source of truth for business-critical metrics
Validate assumptions and ensure data accuracy and consistency
Dashboards & Reporting

Design, maintain, and rationalise dashboards across multiple BI tools
Organise reporting for clarity and usability, reducing noise, not adding to it
Ensure leaders trust the data they're using to make decisions
Insight & Analysis

Proactively analyse data to surface trends, drivers, risks, and opportunities
Translate vague or poorly formed requests into meaningful analysis
Explain why something matters, not just what happened
Commercial & Operational Understanding

Analyse revenue drivers, retention and churn, cost drivers, and operational throughput
Help the business understand efficiency, performance, and scale constraints
Partner with stakeholders to ensure insights are actionable and decision-led
Product & Customer Reporting

Work with Product and Technology teams to inform and improve customer-facing metrics and reports
Ensure external reporting is accurate, meaningful, and aligned with internal definitions
You'll work closely with the CEO and senior leaders and partner with experienced engineers who deeply understand our systems.
 
What we're looking for
You're a senior analyst who has worked in complex, commercial environments and understands the responsibility that comes with owning business-critical data. You're comfortable challenging requests, asking better questions, and prioritising insight over activity.
 
You care about correctness, context, and impact, and you want your work to actually influence decisions.
 
Must-haves

Strong SQL and data interrogation skills
Comfortable querying complex datasets and joining across multiple sources
Proven experience owning data dictionaries and metric definitions
Experience working across multiple BI or data visualisation tools, with deep expertise in at least one
Strong commercial and operational mindset (revenue, retention, costs, efficiency)
Ability to translate vague requests into clear, actionable insight
Confidence to challenge metrics and requests constructively
Focus on data accuracy, validation, and trust
Nice-to-haves

Experience in B2B, SaaS, subscription, or operations-heavy environments
Experience with services + software hybrid businesses
Familiarity with EOS scorecards or similar operating metrics
Light experience with data modelling or transformations (e.g. views, transformations)
Comfort using AI tools (e.g. ChatGPT) to accelerate analysis, validate logic, or explore insights
What this role is (and isn't)
This role is:

A senior ownership role with real influence on decision-making
A mix of analysis, insight, and stakeholder partnership
Focused on quality, clarity, and commercial impact
This role is not:

Pure data visualisation or vanity reporting
A purely academic or research-focused analytics role
A data engineering or infrastructure position
A role measured by dashboard count instead of decision impact
The perks

Salary range: $150,000 - $190,000 + super (depending on experience)
High-impact role in a fast-growing, high-volume business

Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Company Description

KPMG’s Deal Advisory practice is a leading corporate finance adviser in Australia, across its lines of business - Mergers & Acquisitions, Valuations, Infrastructure & Projects, Restructuring, Transaction Services and Debt Advisory Services.

Our Transaction Services team has extensive experience in providing financial due diligence and related services to help clients assess, plan and manage acquisitions, mergers, divestments and initial and secondary debt and equity offerings. We leverage insights from our advanced analytics solutions to provide real-time advice to our clients in a fast-paced environment.

Job Description

We now have an opportunity for an experienced individual to join our team to continue to build our dedicated data analytics capability within Transaction Services. This is an excellent opportunity to join one of the leading corporate advisors in Australia and worldwide and to develop your skills in a diverse range of industries.

Having worked within a professional services firm or corporate environment, you will be involved in and lead the application of advanced data analytics to provide unique insights to our clients on end-to-end projects in relation to:

Financial due diligence

Pre-deal evaluations

Vendor assistance

Strategic and commercial intelligence

Value creation activities

Capital markets assistance

Synergy assessment

Integration assistance

Post deal effectiveness reviews

How are you extraordinary?

You have proven experience in the M&A environment, including transaction services or a commercial team in an operational business or analytics / business intelligence roles.

You have experience working with analytical solutions such as Alteryx and Power BI / Tableau to provide relevant commercial insights

You embrace how our diligence findings impact the deal rationale and associated valuation considerations.

You are looking for a career path in a fast-growing, market leading Transaction Services team working on some of the largest and most exciting deals in Australia and internationally.

You thrive in navigating financial, commercial and people issues to support business opportunities; and

You are excited to help build a high performing team and enjoy teaching and mentoring junior team members.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients, and communities. Our team is searching for experienced professionals with a range of qualifications, skills & experiences, including:

Experience using analytical solutions and techniques to conduct financial analysis in a M&A environment to provide deeper insight.

Have had experience with Alteryx, visualization tools (e.g., Tableau or Power BI) to prepare detailed financial analysis. Additional working knowledge of Python, VBA etc. would be beneficial, but not necessary.

Ability to work independently and take initiative, demonstrating strong problem-solving and decision-making skills.

The ability to build robust relationships at all levels, internally and externally.

Recent professional experience in Big 4 / independent corporate advisory, accounting or law firms, investment banking, or within commercial teams in operational businesses.

A desire to contribute to team success along with a motivated and dedicated work ethic.

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification in Commerce/Finance/Accounting or Data Science or Business Analytics related discipline.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Project Reporting Analyst (Contract)

6 month contract with possible extension.

Melbourne CBD / Hybrid


We are seeking an experienced Project Reporting Analyst to support a large service transformation program within a Victorian public sector organisation.

This role focuses on program and project governance reporting, providing clear and accurate insights to senior leaders to support decision-making and oversight. You will work closely with program leadership, project managers and delivery teams to consolidate reporting, track performance, and highlight risks and dependencies.

Key responsibilities


Prepare and deliver regular program and project governance reports for senior executives
Consolidate inputs from multiple workstreams into clear, decision-ready summaries
Track delivery status, risks, issues, dependencies, milestones and resourcing
Develop and maintain reporting templates, dashboards and performance metrics
Support program governance forums through preparation of packs and action tracking
Maintain central repositories for program documentation and decisions
Identify opportunities to improve reporting quality, consistency and efficiency

Key requirements


Strong experience in program or portfolio reporting within complex environments
Proven ability to communicate delivery status clearly to executive audiences
Experience working across multiple projects and stakeholders
Solid understanding of project delivery methods including Agile and Waterfall
Strong analytical skills with attention to detail
Experience using tools such as Jira, MS Project, Power BI and Confluence
Public sector or regulated environment experience highly regarded

This is a hands-on role suited to someone who enjoys turning complex delivery information into clear, meaningful reporting.


Please apply with current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). If you would like to have a confidential discussion, please contact Krunal Patel on krunal.patel@davidsonwp.com, quoting reference JN -012026-42147. Want to know more about Davidson? Visit us at www.davidsonwp.com

Job Title: General Manager, Policy and Analysis Branch, Net Zero Economy Authority
Company: Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet
Ad Text:
Step into a pivotal leadership role as General Manager, Policy and Analysis with the Net Zero Economy Authority, where you’ll drive national policy and data strategy at the forefront of Australia’s economic and social transformation. This is your opportunity to shape the Authority’s policy agenda, lead high-performing teams, and deliver evidence-based insights that support workers, communities, and industries through the net zero transition. You’ll collaborate with senior officials, industry, and regional leaders, ensuring decisions are informed by robust analysis and innovative thinking. If you’re a strategic, values-driven leader with a passion for public sector impact and a commitment to building a better future, this high-profile executive position offers the chance to make a lasting difference.

Flexibility arrangements

Flexible work is a broad term used to describe a variety of different arrangements about how, when and where work is performed. The authority supports mutually beneficial flexible work arrangements which suit operational requirements. Arrangements may be consistent and regular, such as part time work, working from home a couple of days each week or remotely from another location; or more ad hoc such as varying work attendance times or occasional home based work. Consideration is given to all flexible work requests, approval is not limited to an employee’s classification level or caring responsibilities.

Eligibility

This role is being advertised as both ongoing and non-ongoing. The role may be offered as either ongoing or non-ongoing subject to business needs and/or candidate preference. Where a non-ongoing position is offered, the role will be filled as a specified term vacancy for an initial period of up to 12 months.
Under section 22(8) of the Public Service Act 1999, employees must be Australian citizens to be employed in the Australian Public Service (APS) unless the Agency Head has agreed otherwise, in writing. At NZEA (PM&C) to be eligible for this position you should be an Australian Citizen at the closing date of application, unless exceptional circumstances apply (see FAQs in the candidate information pack for more details).
Successful applicants will be required to undergo the process to obtain and maintain, or continue to hold the required security clearance level for the role as indicated. All NZEA staff are required to have a minimum baseline security clearance prior to commencement.
Successful applicants will be assessed through our pre-employment screening checks, including a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check, and will normally be subject to a six-month probation period if new to the APS, or if they have not yet completed their probation period elsewhere in the APS.

How to apply

If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, submit an online application through the Apply link by Sunday, 18 January 2026 at 11:30pm AEDT.

Senior Financial Analyst - 6-Month Contract

Location: Artarmon, NSW

Work Arrangement: Hybrid

Contract:Temporary (6 months)

Your new company
Join a global leader in the industrial sector that is committed to innovation and excellence. This organisation offers a collaborative environment and the flexibility of hybrid working.

Your new role
As a Senior Financial Analyst, you will provide critical financial insights and analysis to support strategic decision-making. This is a 6-month temporary contract where you will work closely with senior stakeholders and contribute to key projects.


Key responsibilities include:

Preparing and analysing financial reports to support business performance
Monthly balance sheet reconciliations
Conducting variance analysis and identifying key trends
Assisting with budgeting, forecasting, and month-end processes
Supporting strategic initiatives and providing financial modelling
Collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver accurate and timely insights

What you'll need to succeed

CA/CPA or equivalent
Must be immediately available
3-5 years of commercial experience post qualification
SAP experience preferred
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Advanced Excel and financial modelling capabilities
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills

What you'll get in return

Competitive daily rate
Hybrid working arrangement
Opportunity to work with a global leader in the industrial sector
Exposure to strategic projects and senior leadership

New year, new opportunity to grow your career in a dynamic and supportive multinational with excellent career progression!

About your new Employer!
  
This multinational, product-based organisation is a leader in its category across the APAC region. With strong year-on-year growth, complex operations and a genuinely collaborative culture, the business is investing heavily in commercial finance capability to support strategic decision-making. You’ll join a high-performing finance team that values curiosity, continuous improvement, and evidence-based insight. This is an environment where your recommendations influence senior leadership and directly shape future business outcomes.
  
About your new Role!
  
We’re looking for an experienced Finance Business Partner to step into a highly analytical, commercially impactful role with APAC-wide scope. Reporting directly to the CFO, you’ll work alongside multiple Finance Business Partners and will be the one who brings it all together. Your mandate is to take large volumes of operational and commercial data, analyse it, interpret it, and convert it into clear, actionable insights that support strategic and operational decision-making.
  
This role exists because the CFO needs more than just data, he needs meaningful stories, informed recommendations, and an ability to provide insights that influence business outcomes.
  
Key responsibilities include:

Business partnering across sales, operations, logistics and commercial teams
Analysing large datasets and distilling insights to support decision-making
Leading and coordinating the full planning process across APAC
Assessing the quality and reliability of sales forecasts and market assumptions
Supporting Sales & Operations Planning (S&OP) with commercial insight
CAPEX analysis, evaluation and recommendations
Identifying performance improvement opportunities and providing strategic suggestions
Storytelling: presenting insights in a compelling, logical, and impactful way
  
About You!

Professional qualification such as CA, CPA, CFA is desirable but not essential
3-5 years experience in a commercial role such as Finance Business Partner, Commercial Analyst, Commercial Manager
Highly analytical capability with experience working across large, complex datasets
Proven ability to convert numbers into commercial stories, insights and recommendations
Product based industry experience such as FMCG, Consumer Goods,  Manufacturing or similar is highly desirable
Strong understanding of planning cycles, forecasting and long-term modelling
Demonstrated ability to influence senior stakeholders and guide others through the planning process
Curious, commercially minded and proactive; constantly questioning how performance can be improved
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement skills
  
What’s in it for You?

Circa. $160,000 – $175,000 base + super + bonus
High-impact role with direct influence on APAC strategy
Work closely with a commercial, forward-thinking CFO
Clear and tangible career progression opportunities
Collaborative culture with strong executive exposure
Hybrid working arrangement | Close to Public Transport
Please APPLY NOW or contact Declan Stacey on 0483 945 773 for more information.

Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 280 million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.

We are looking for a Data Scientist expert to drive advancements in natural language processing and computer vision. You’ll work across content understanding scenarios such as classification, entity recognition, sentiment analysis, and image/video understanding, and help build large-scale systems that power content moderation, recommendation, and search.

Develop and optimize NLP/CV algorithms to improve the performance and efficiency of content understanding pipelines.
Build scalable models (e.g., BERT, GPT, ViT, CLIP) and bring them into production.
Partner with product and data teams to diagnose business challenges and design data-driven solutions.
Track cutting-edge research and explore novel algorithms for real-world applications in content understanding.
Drive system improvements that enhance moderation, recommendation and search workflow
Master’s Degree or above in Computer Science, AI, EE, Mathematics, or related fields.
Strong programming skills in Python or C++ and familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch.
Solid foundation in machine learning/deep learning and hands-on experience with common models in NLP and/or CV.
Experience working with large-scale data processing frameworks (Hadoop/Spark/Flink is a plus).
2+ years of algorithm/model development experience.
Background in content safety, recommendation or search systems is highly valued.

Why Binance

• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem

• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure

• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment

• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning

• Competitive salary and company benefits

• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)
